  "texts": [
    "Based on its reasoning, Orchestrator selects a tool from the available set (e.g., APIs, specialized models, code interpreters) and specifies parameters.",
    "(3) Tool response (observation).",
    "If a tool call is present, the tool-call block is extracted and executed by the environment; the resulting output is appended to the context under the user role and fed back to the model for the next turn.",
    "This process repeats until Orchestrator receives a termination signal from the environment or the rollout reaches a maximum of 50 turns.",
    "ToolOrchestraOur approach, ToolOrchestra, centers on training a small language model as an intelligent agentic model capable of solving complex tasks by dynamically selecting and utilizing a wide variety of external tools.We hypothesize that small language models suffice for this purpose if they are taught to coordinate more intelligent tools strategically, and thus choose to train an 8B model."
